name Blackberry Sauce
serves 4
tags sauce

# Preparation

- 1 tbsp butter
- 100 g blackberries
Melt the butter, add the blackberries and steam for
about 5 minutes.

- 2 tbsp cognac
- 100 ml red wine
- 200 ml beef stock
Add the cognac, wine and stock, bring to a boil and reduce by half.

- 2 tbsp blackberry jelly
- 100 ml creme fraiche
- 50 g blackberries
- "cayenne pepper"
- salt
Stir in the jelly and the creme fraiche and add the remaining blackberries. 
Heat through without boiling. Season with cayenne and salt.
